GOVERNMENTS THE world over are beefing up defence spending—chief among them America’s and China’s. But some of the usual big military spenders are actually shrinking budgets. May Day protests in France took a violent turn this year, and that complicates President Macron’s efforts to calm an already protest-prone populace. And academics have been trying to determine which English-speaking country produces the most bullshit. Runtime: 21min.    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn